@node Introduction
                 
                                @{u}INTRODUCTION@{uu}
                 
           
 @{b}WHAT DOES IT DO..............@{ub}

     It tries to Play OctaMed and Protracker Modules using a mixture of
     Assembly language routines and library calls.
     
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}
     
     
     @{fg shine}@{i}Great yet other Module Player and whats so good about this one then

     Err well.@{ui}@{fg text}

     *  Its small compact size. 
     
     *  The author is so sad he's tested it on just about every type of
        Octamed & Protracker Module. 
       
     *  It makes loads of checks and informs the user if anything go's
        wrong (most of the time).
        
     *  Checks Fastmem loading/Playing and turns on/off accordingly.
        
     *  The user has a choice of using the simple window displayed on 
        opening or clicking on the more gadget for extra goodies.
        
     *  Its got a very simple user interface.         
               
               
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}              

                             @{"BACK TO INDEX" link Main}
@endnode

@node Installation
                             
                      @{b}Taffys Player (Installing it).@{ub}
      

     Installing this program is very easy you should have no problems just
     drag the Taffys Player Icon wherever you wish it to go on your Hard
     Disk.
    
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}


 @{b}LIBRARIES....................@{ub}
 
     All the Libraries you need should already be in your sys/libs Drawer
     on your hard disk.
     If not the program will tell you what version number you need
     here's a list anyway.  
 
     * @{" medplayer.library " link Medplayer.library}     v7.1    4  Channels
     
     * @{" octaplayer.library " link  octaplayer.library}    v7.1    8  Channels
     
     * @{" octamixplayer.library " link  octamixplayer.library} v7.1    64 Channels
     
     * @{" ptreplay.library " link ptreplay.library}      v6.6    4  Channels 
 
     -  gadtools.library      v39
     -  asl.library           v40
     -  dos.library           v39    ;
     -  intuition.library     v40    ;
     
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}
            
            
 @{b}OBTAINING LIBRARIES...........@{ub}      
 
     You can obtain the player librarys needed from the following.......
              
                 
 @{b}AMIGA FORMAT..................@{ub} 
  
     Cover CDs 41-49 in :+System+/Libs  for :- ptreplay.library v6.6.
     
     medplayer.library * octaplayer.library * octamix.library. 
     
     can also be found in various draws on the above cds.
     
          
 @{b}The AMINET....................@{ub}    
     
     The Aminet also contains all the above librarys.
     
     
 @{b}OTHER SITES...................@{ub}    
     
     For the Octamed librarys try Http://www.Octamed.co.uk   
     
                         
                             @{"BACK TO INDEX" link Main}    
@endnode

@node Features

                               @{b}FEATURES@{ub} 
                             
     After loading a supported module you are able to PLAY STOP CONTINUE      
     from the small window.
                    
          
 @{b}CUSTOM WINDOW................@{ub}
               
     Clicking on the "MORE" gadget after loading a supported module     
     opens a custom window with adjustable options for the module loaded.
                                                            
     @{" Four Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link FourChannel}
     @{" Eight Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link EightChannel }
     @{" Mix mode (64) Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link sixtyfourChannel}
     @{" Protracker Module." link protracker}
     @{" General Module Information displayed on every window." link General}        
   
                         
 @{b}SUPPORTED MODULES............@{ub}

     *  Four Channel Octamed Module's using   @{" Medplayer.library." link medplayer.library}     v7.1

     *  Eight Channel Octamed Module's using  @{" Octaplayer.library." link octaplayer.library}    v7.1
     
     *  Sixty Four Channel Modules using      @{" Octamixplayer.library." link  octamixplayer.library} v7.1  
         
     *  Four Channel Protracker Modules using @{" ptreplay.library." link ptreplay.library}      v6.6 

     
 @{b}FILE ID'S SUPPORTED..........@{ub} 
     
     *  MMD0 MMD1 MMD2 MMD3 M.K. 
               
            
 @{b}AUTOMATIC CHECKS.............@{ub}
                                       
     * @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay} on/off at loading. 
             
     *  Load Fastram check before loading.
             
     *  Does not rely on the MMD id for Module Replaying or loading.
             
     *  Automatically loads to Fastram if Chip to Small and turns on
       @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay}.
                        
     @{fg shine}*@{fg text}  (Hope to add Load and play Fast RAM for Octamed Modules.) 
         
         
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}
                                                                  
                             @{"BACK TO INDEX" link Main}
@endnode
                  
@node   FourChannel                    

        @{b}Options for 4 Channel Octamed Module (medplayer Library v7.1).@{ub}
            
                     
 @{b}CYCLE GADGETS................@{ub}
                                                     
     * @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay}         Turns @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay} on/off.
     
     *  Reset MIDI             Not available in this version.
     
     * @{" LowPass Filter " link Audio Filter}       Toggles lowpass filter on/off. 
                               The Module Playing will override this 
                               setting if lowpass filtering is used by the
                               Module.
                               
                               
 @{b}INTEGER GADGETS..............@{ub}                             

     *  Fast Memory Play       Change the size of the Fast memory
        Buffer Size            Play buffer. See :- @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay}

                                         
 @{b}BUTTON GADGETS...............@{ub}                      
               
     *  Apply Changes          Affects all the changes made with the cycle
                               and integer gadgets (Not Filter).
                               Divide's the integer contents by four checks
                               max min.
                               Stops the Module if Playing calls library
                               routine's required.
              
     *  PLAY                   Plays the currently loaded Module.
             
     *  STOP                   Stops the currently Playing Module.
             
     *  CONT                   Continues the Module from current Position.
              
     *  EJECT                  Stops/Ejects/Unloads Module free's Player
                               Closes Player library.
                           
                           
 @{b}PLEASE NOTE..................@{ub} 
  
     @{fg shine}@{i}These options are only available by clicking on the more gadget
     when a supported Module is loaded.@{ui}@{fg text}
                                       
     When Playing Module from first window after adjusting the above 
     settings.  
              
     * @{" LowPass Filter " link Audio Filter} on/off is Ignored.
              
     *  Any Buffer size changes or @{" Fastmem Play " link fastmemplay} state will remain as set
        by this window.
                               
                               
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub} 
                     
                           @{"BACK TO INDEX" link Main}
@endnode

@node  General
                          
                       @{b}General Module Attributes@{ub}

                            
 @{b}ATTRIBUTES...................@{ub}   
                                         
     *  Module Size            Size of Module in Bytes. 
         
     *  Instruments            Number of Samples,Synth sounds used.
          
     *  Num Blocks             Number of Blocks used.
          
     *  Playing Seq            Number of Blocks in sequence.
        
     *  Module File Type       Type of Module loaded.
        
     *  Memory Type            Type of Memory used Chip or Fast.
        
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}
            
            
 @{b}PLEASE NOTE.................@{ub}
 
     *  Playing Sel is used instead of Playing Seq in Modules with file
        type MMD2 and MMD3. Which is the number of Sequences Used.    
                 
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}
                             
                           @{"BACK TO INDEX" link Main}                     
@endnode

