@node  fastmemplay

                              @{b}FASTMEM PLAY@{ub}


 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  Enables or disables Fastmem playing, and sets the size of the
        output buffer 4 to 400 divisible by four.(rounded by program.)
        
     *  Enabling allows samples greater than 131,072 bytes to be played in
        chip or fast ram.
        
     *	Changes made only applied to module by clicking on the APPLY CHANGES
	gadget. 
	
        @{fg shine}@{i}Only available in 4 and 8 Channel Octamed Modules.@{ui}@{fg text}
        
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
               
                            
@endnode
@node  Audio Filter

                              @{b}LOWPASS FILTER@{ub}


 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  Toggling the Amiga's lowpass filter off/on done by this 
        (bchg #1,$BFE001). Sorry !
     
     *  Lowpass filter works by reducing the high frequencies.     
                      
     *  Enabling the lowpass filter smooths the sound but reduces the volume. 
                 
     *	Enabling the lowpass filter eliminates buzz at low sample rates. 
	 	
     *	Modules which toggle filter on/off will override filter setting.
     
     *  Lowpass filter is set off when playing from first window.
                
            @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
               
                            
@endnode
@node  HQ Mode

               @{b}HIGH QUALITY MODE (8 CHANNEL OCTAMED MODULE)@{ub}


 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  Enabling smooths out the sound but takes up processor time.
     
     *  An A1200 68020 is needed.     
                      
     *  Significantly increases the audio quality. 
                 
     *	Enabling reduces volume of Module. 
     
     *	Changes made only applied to module by clicking on the APPLY CHANGES
	gadget.
	 	
                 @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
@endnode
@node  Set14BitMode

                    @{b}14 BITMODE (64 CHANNEL OCTAMED MODULE)@{ub}

 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  The sound is much louder when turned off but suffers from distortion.
     
     *  An A1200 68020 is needed.     
                      
     *  Enabling significantly increases the audio quality. 
                 
     *	Enabling reduces volume of Module. 
           
     *	Changes made only applied to module by clicking on the APPLY CHANGES
	gadget.	
	 	
                 @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
@endnode
@node  MixBuffer64

                    @{b}MIX BUFFER (64 CHANNEL OCTAMED MODULE)@{ub}

 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  An area of memory used to mix samples together before output.
     
     *  An A1200 68020 is the min spec here but still a bit slow.  
     
     *  Default of 1024 is adequate for most Modules.
     
     *  Values between 4-32768 can be entered.    
                             	 	
     *	Changes made only applied to module by clicking on the APPLY CHANGES
	gadget.           
	             	 	
                 @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
@endnode
@node  Mixing frequency

                 @{b}MIXING FREQUENCY (64 CHANNEL OCTAMED MODULE)@{ub}

 @{b}FUNCTION.....................@{ub}

     *  Specifies in Hertz how quickly the samples should be mixed.
     
     *  An A1200 68020 is the min spec here but still a bit slow.  
     
     *  The higher the frequency the better the sound quality the more
        processor load.
     
     *  Highest possible frequency depends on the screen mode in use.
     
     *  Maximum value program allows you to use is 28375. 
     
     *  Values between 1000-65535 can be entered. 
                             	 	
     *	Changes made only applied to module by clicking on the APPLY CHANGES
	gadget.       
	                 	 	
                 @{b}-----------------------------------------------@{ub}  
@endnode
               
                            
